It sucks to know I PAID to have some tables because they didn't tip. 
I honestly can't wait to get a new job because it is so disheartening.

Multiple tables who tipped less than 10%.

I know this is a financially difficult time for everyone, but if you can't afford to tip your servers you should not be going out to dinner. 

I tip out 8% of my total sales to the rest of the staff regardless if I am tipped or not.

My tips in general last night were ABYSMAL! 
I felt I was doing such a good job and being really positive even though it was an emotionally difficult day for me and it sucked to not see that reflected whatsoever. 
Multiple tables who didn't tip at all.

At work last night (at a restaurant on Valentine's day) I was serving this table with a really nice couple, and the guy was SO nice to me, talking about how great my service was constantly. I was so happy they were happy!

You know how much they tipped me?

so if you havent tipped, that's just coming out of my money. 

Basically, it's a shitty system, and I get that everyone isnt in a great financial spot right now, but if you can't afford to tip you should not be going out for dinner.

I feel like I didnt explain well in the first tweet but basically they will have to pay out a percentage based on sales. So if I'm your server, if your table spent $40 a percentage of that will automatically be charged out to other staff from my tip pool,

they have essentially paid to have your table. 
Hopefully I've explained this so it makes sense but man, I've been having an extra rough time with tips since going back to work and it's really disheartening.

One thing I wish more people realized about how tipping works at many places, is that your server will have to pay out a percentage to FOH and BOH staff regardless if you tip them or not. So if they get no tip from you, they are not only making less than min wage but also
